# Copy to .env.local for local dev, or set in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production / Preview).
# Build-time: Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_.
#
# --- Frontend-only Vercel project (Root Directory = "frontend") ---
# Point the UI at your separate backend URL (include /api/v1):
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-project.vercel.app/api/v1
# Set backend cors_origins to include this frontend origin (e.g. https://your-frontend.vercel.app).
#
# --- Backend-only Vercel project (same repo, Root Directory = empty / repo root) ---
# Uses repo-root vercel.json (Python only). No npm. Ensure PYTHONPATH / imports work; ai/ lives next to backend/.

# Default for local Vite proxy (see vite.config.ts):
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api/v1

# Optional. If unset, WebSocket URL is derived from VITE_API_BASE_URL.
# VITE_WS_BASE_URL=wss://your-backend-project.vercel.app
